@MarioNawfal The timing does line up, but oil markets react to many variables at once.

OPEC+ supply decisions move prices more than ceasefire timing does.

Reading pauses as market management gives too much credit to coordination that rarely exists.

@Jake__Wujastyk Does it matter which kind of gap fill, though? 

Oil ripping on a demand signal is bullish for SPY/QQQ — real growth story. Oil ripping on a supply shock (OPEC, geopolitical) drags the same names via inflation/rate fears. 

Same $83.20 print, opposite equity read.
